5
00:00:17,559 --> 00:00:19,978
MIYAKO AIRPORT

6
00:00:21,313 --> 00:00:22,981
We've arrived!

7
00:00:23,148 --> 00:00:26,818
-So this is Miyakojima.
-It's pretty far away.

8
00:00:26,985 --> 00:00:29,988
Riding a plane within the same prefecture is weird.

9
00:00:31,323 --> 00:00:34,076
This island is closer to Taiwan than Japan.

10
00:00:34,243 --> 00:00:35,994
No wonder it was so far!

11
00:00:36,912 --> 00:00:39,748
-Sorry.
-We didn't notice we were doing it.

12
00:00:39,915 --> 00:00:42,501
We're going to dive now. You can't drink.

13
00:00:42,668 --> 00:00:45,462
You guys fit right in now.

14
00:00:48,298 --> 00:00:50,092
Hey, you guys!

15
00:00:50,259 --> 00:00:52,219
It looks like you arrived safely.

16
00:00:55,055 --> 00:00:58,809
-Thanks for coming.
-No problem.

17
00:00:58,976 --> 00:01:01,645
We got here last night.

18
00:01:01,812 --> 00:01:05,023
-You got here pretty early.
-We're going diving in the morning.

19
00:01:05,190 --> 00:01:06,942
We wanted to get here a day early.

20
00:01:07,109 --> 00:01:10,404
We're looking forward to Otori afterwards even more.

21
00:01:10,570 --> 00:01:11,655
-Otori?
-Otori?

22
00:01:11,822 --> 00:01:15,450
-It's a drinking custom from Miyakojima.
-Haven't you heard about it?

23
00:01:15,617 --> 00:01:19,288
Otori is one of the main reasons
we came on this trip.

24
00:01:20,038 --> 00:01:21,248
WHAT IS OTORI!

25
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:24,001
-So that's what it was!
-So that's what it was!

26
00:01:26,962 --> 00:01:29,339
By the way, I saw some rumors on the Internet

27
00:01:29,506 --> 00:01:33,343
that some restaurants put out signs saying
"No Miyakojima people."

28
00:01:33,510 --> 00:01:36,179
Is it because Otori is too wild?

29
00:01:36,346 --> 00:01:38,432
That's just an urban legend.

30
00:01:38,598 --> 00:01:41,184
No one would drink and act that badly.

31
00:01:41,351 --> 00:01:42,644
You're right....

32
00:01:42,811 --> 00:01:43,895
NO PaB MEMBERS

33
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:47,774
-What did you guys do last night?
-What did you guys do last night?

34
00:01:48,108 --> 00:01:53,155
-Well, enough of that.
-It's finally time to make your debut as divers.

35
00:01:53,739 --> 00:01:55,574
About that. Actually...

36
00:01:55,741 --> 00:01:58,452
He had a fever yesterday and stayed in bed.

37
00:01:58,618 --> 00:02:01,496
-Really?
-So you didn't get your license?

38
00:02:01,663 --> 00:02:03,332
This is embarrassing...

39
00:02:03,498 --> 00:02:06,835
-I was looking forward to it a little too much.
-What do you mean?

40
00:02:07,002 --> 00:02:09,046
Getting sick on a trip? Like a little kid?

41
00:02:09,379 --> 00:02:12,090
That's why I can't go diving with you.

42
00:02:12,257 --> 00:02:15,010
-I see.
-That's too bad.

43
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:23,060
Wow, it's so fast!

44
00:02:23,226 --> 00:02:25,520
The wind feels really good!

45
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:27,314
What did you say?

46
00:02:28,273 --> 00:02:29,566
You're too close!

47
00:02:30,776 --> 00:02:33,779
-The amateur is getting excited.
-What?

48
00:02:33,945 --> 00:02:35,572
I heard you!

49
00:02:35,864 --> 00:02:37,949
You've only done it twice yourself!

50
00:02:38,116 --> 00:02:42,079
Want me to teach the amateur
how to behave on the boat?

51
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:45,832
Stop it! There are other people here too!

52
00:02:46,958 --> 00:02:48,377
All right, everyone.

53
00:02:48,543 --> 00:02:50,879
Let's begin our meeting!

54
00:02:51,046 --> 00:02:52,923
Okay!

55
00:02:55,801 --> 00:02:58,095
That's what it's going to be like.

56
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:03,558
We're planning to dive to a depth of 17 meters
for 40 minutes.

57
00:03:04,434 --> 00:03:07,354
All right, everyone. Please get ready!

58
00:03:07,521 --> 00:03:09,064
Okay!

59
00:03:09,231 --> 00:03:12,150
Okay, okay! Let's go change in the dressing room!

60
00:03:12,401 --> 00:03:15,278
-What are you going to do?
-About what?

61
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:18,490
You have to have a license to dive 17 meters.

62
00:03:18,657 --> 00:03:20,367
I'll be okay.

63
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:24,538
They're letting me join their trial dives
for the first and second dives.

64
00:03:24,704 --> 00:03:26,665
What about the third dive?

65
00:03:26,832 --> 00:03:29,376
Everyone's planning to go on three dives.

66
00:03:29,543 --> 00:03:31,753
I'll just wait on the boat.

67
00:03:32,087 --> 00:03:34,923
Maybe I should ask them to let me join them too.

68
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:39,177
-Why?
-I'm not confident I'll be able to dive well.

69
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,012
What are you talking about?

70
00:03:41,388 --> 00:03:45,016
The guys will help you, and you have her too.

71
00:03:46,226 --> 00:03:48,061
The ocean is so beautiful here.

72
00:03:48,228 --> 00:03:50,147
You should go as far as you can.

73
00:03:51,273 --> 00:03:52,065
Okay.

74
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:55,235
Everyone who's here for the trial dive,
gather here please!

75
00:03:56,611 --> 00:03:59,156
Bye. Have fun!

76
00:04:08,999 --> 00:04:12,335
Go slow and stay calm.
Let's equalize pressure.

77
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,296
Okay!

78
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:49,456
The sea turtles came really close.

79
00:04:49,623 --> 00:04:51,625
That was amazing!

80
00:04:51,791 --> 00:04:53,877
We were lucky to see a parent with a child.

81
00:04:54,044 --> 00:04:56,796
It's as amazing as 2D!

82
00:04:56,963 --> 00:04:59,633
Were you able to see it, Iori?

83
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:03,720
-No. Too bad.
-We took pictures. Here.

84
00:05:03,887 --> 00:05:05,096
It looked like this.

85
00:05:06,348 --> 00:05:08,642
I wish I could've seen that up close.

86
00:05:08,808 --> 00:05:11,937
If you get your license,
you'll have another chance.

87
00:05:12,103 --> 00:05:14,439
Work harder next time, junior.

88
00:05:14,606 --> 00:05:17,651
Hearing you, of all people, say that really pisses me off.

89
00:05:21,363 --> 00:05:23,365
I'll get the tea.

90
00:05:42,717 --> 00:05:44,553
This looks just like the aquarium.

91
00:05:47,722 --> 00:05:50,600
I want to see it up close next time.

92
00:05:55,438 --> 00:05:58,775
He can't see it from over there...

93
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:08,618
That was so magical.

94
00:06:08,785 --> 00:06:11,204
It makes me wish I had a camera!

95
00:06:11,371 --> 00:06:14,249
The light is just right at this time of day.

96
00:06:14,416 --> 00:06:16,710
You don't get to see that every day.

97
00:06:16,876 --> 00:06:18,712
Where's Iori?

98
00:06:18,878 --> 00:06:21,131
He said he was going to rest on the deck.

99
00:06:21,339 --> 00:06:23,550
I see.

100
00:06:23,717 --> 00:06:26,136
Iori has been pretty quiet today.

101
00:06:26,303 --> 00:06:27,470
You're right.

102
00:06:27,637 --> 00:06:30,056
Maybe he's feeling sick.

103
00:06:31,850 --> 00:06:34,853
-Nanaka.
-What's wrong, Chisa-chan?

104
00:06:35,020 --> 00:06:37,897
I'm going to skip the third dive.

105
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,317
My ears ache.

106
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:56,916
You know, Iori...

107
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:02,213
It's too bad you couldn't dive with everyone today,
but this isn't the last time.

108
00:07:04,341 --> 00:07:09,012
We're going somewhere shallow tomorrow
where you can do more trial dives.

109
00:07:10,597 --> 00:07:12,390
That's right!

110
00:07:12,557 --> 00:07:15,810
I got tickets to the aquarium
at work the other day.

111
00:07:15,977 --> 00:07:17,145
If you want...

112
00:07:17,854 --> 00:07:18,730
Chisa.

113
00:07:20,940 --> 00:07:23,652
The boat really rocks back and forth...

114
00:07:26,946 --> 00:07:30,867
I should have taken the motion sickness pills
like they told me to.

115
00:07:31,034 --> 00:07:33,620
Waiting on the surface before diving...

116
00:07:33,787 --> 00:07:37,666
-That's pretty rough too.
-Iori.

117
00:07:37,999 --> 00:07:41,544
-What?
-Are you just seasick?

118
00:07:41,711 --> 00:07:45,423
What do you mean "just"? I feel horrible.

119
00:07:49,928 --> 00:07:52,180
-Come on.
-Sorry.

120
00:07:52,889 --> 00:07:55,100
Well, you know, Chisa...

121
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:01,022
You're a good woman.

122
00:08:01,981 --> 00:08:05,110
What? What are you talking about?

123
00:08:05,276 --> 00:08:08,697
You were thinking about me when I was left here alone.

124
00:08:10,323 --> 00:08:12,325
Well, not really.

125
00:08:12,492 --> 00:08:14,703
Don't worry, Chisa.

126
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:19,249
I'm not going to hate diving
just because of this.

127
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:23,712
I see.

128
00:08:24,170 --> 00:08:26,464
Diving is amazing.

129
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:31,344
-I never imagined it'd be fun on the boat as well.
-The boat?

130
00:08:31,511 --> 00:08:35,014
When we were coming here just now,
I thought to myself...

131
00:08:35,181 --> 00:08:37,976
Talking about what you saw underwater...

132
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:40,979
Eating lunch together on the boat...

133
00:08:41,396 --> 00:08:44,482
Feeling the breeze and the sunlight
while the boat moves...

134
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:47,402
It feels amazing.

135
00:08:49,696 --> 00:08:53,116
The guys are usually loud, but they're so relaxed.

136
00:08:53,283 --> 00:08:55,994
They're like sunbathing cats.

137
00:08:56,661 --> 00:08:59,372
It's too bad I could only participate in the trial dive.

138
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:02,167
-But I want to come again.
-I see.

139
00:09:02,333 --> 00:09:06,296
You didn't go on the third dive either,
so you would want to come again too, right?

140
00:09:06,463 --> 00:09:08,631
Well, yeah.

141
00:09:11,301 --> 00:09:13,178
If you treat me.

142
00:09:13,344 --> 00:09:16,389
You know I don't have much. How can you say that?

143
00:09:16,723 --> 00:09:19,851
I'll take you if I win the lottery.

144
00:09:20,935 --> 00:09:23,021
I'm not going to get my hopes up.

145
00:09:24,773 --> 00:09:28,610
All right, everyone! We're done diving now!

146
00:09:28,777 --> 00:09:30,278
Let's head back to land!

147
00:09:30,445 --> 00:09:31,905
Okay!

148
00:09:54,219 --> 00:09:55,887
Hey, everyone. Listen.

149
00:09:56,513 --> 00:10:00,433
It's about Otori.
One of the main reasons we came to Miyakojima.

150
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:06,147
The restaurant we were planning to go to is closed,
so we had to cancel those plans.

151
00:10:08,149 --> 00:10:11,903
-Otori means endless drinking, right?
-Yeah.

152
00:10:12,070 --> 00:10:14,906
We escaped an endless World Championship.

153
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:18,493
It's going to be a peaceful night on Miyakojima tonight--

154
00:10:18,660 --> 00:10:20,995
But, we don't come to Miyakojima every day.

155
00:10:21,162 --> 00:10:24,666
So let's do our own Otori!

156
00:10:33,842 --> 00:10:36,970
Hey, don't go so crazy, freshman.

157
00:10:37,136 --> 00:10:39,931
Well, then. Let's begin.

158
00:10:43,351 --> 00:10:45,979
What do you mean, "our own Otori"?

159
00:10:46,145 --> 00:10:49,983
-Don't get so agitated.
-We're about to explain.

160
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:52,944
We're going to drink from the same pot.

161
00:10:53,111 --> 00:10:55,154
Especially since it’s a special trip.

162
00:10:55,321 --> 00:10:57,991
You mean like eating from the same bowl?

163
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:03,246
-By the way...
-It's hard to find a drink that everyone likes.

164
00:11:03,413 --> 00:11:04,998
That's true.

165
00:11:05,164 --> 00:11:08,793
It would be sad if not everyone has a good time.

166
00:11:08,960 --> 00:11:10,920
I guess you're right.

167
00:11:11,087 --> 00:11:13,423
We want to make good drinking memories.

168
00:11:13,590 --> 00:11:16,759
-So we came up with an idea.
-To be fair...

169
00:11:16,926 --> 00:11:20,889
we're going to drink something everyone hates!

170
00:11:21,055 --> 00:11:23,766
That's what you're doing to be fair?

171
00:11:23,933 --> 00:11:26,269
We're going to spin this pot,

172
00:11:26,436 --> 00:11:28,855
and have you pour in your favorite drink.

173
00:11:29,022 --> 00:11:32,775
When you do, say a few words. Whatever you want.

174
00:11:32,942 --> 00:11:33,985
A few words?

175
00:11:34,152 --> 00:11:37,113
In Otori, you're supposed to say a few words.

176
00:11:37,280 --> 00:11:40,241
Like, "This is for the beautiful island and the ocean!"

177
00:11:40,408 --> 00:11:41,784
I see.

178
00:11:41,951 --> 00:11:45,622
We're going to say a few serious things first.

179
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,957
We all come from different places,

180
00:11:48,124 --> 00:11:51,044
but we have gathered together
in the same time and place.

181
00:11:51,210 --> 00:11:55,673
I'm happy we could ride on the same boat,
and drink from the same pot.

182
00:11:55,840 --> 00:12:00,678
Everyone here is a comrade and a friend.

183
00:12:00,845 --> 00:12:03,681
Even if life leads us down separate paths,

184
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:07,226
the time we spent together will never disappear.

185
00:12:08,061 --> 00:12:11,648
As a memory of your youth!

186
00:12:11,814 --> 00:12:13,733
Don't ever forget today!

187
00:12:13,900 --> 00:12:14,567
SPIRYTUS (96%)

188
00:12:14,734 --> 00:12:15,693
Yeah!

189
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:19,072
-Idiots!
-What do you mean, "memories of youth"?

190
00:12:19,238 --> 00:12:21,950
You won't remember anything after drinking so much!

191
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:25,787
I'll never forget the time I spent with you guys!

192
00:12:25,954 --> 00:12:26,621
SPIRYTUS (96%)

193
00:12:26,788 --> 00:12:29,958
-Why are you pouring that in?
-You don't really plan on remembering this, do you?

194
00:12:30,124 --> 00:12:32,460
-I-- Azuma...
-Yeah?

195
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,464
-What's wrong, Azuma?
-I...

196
00:12:36,631 --> 00:12:39,092
spent all my time studying chemistry.

197
00:12:39,258 --> 00:12:42,220
I don't know what to say at times like these.

198
00:12:42,387 --> 00:12:44,180
So at least...

199
00:12:44,597 --> 00:12:46,432
I'm going to do whatever I can!

200
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,767
ETHANOL (FOR SANITATION)

201
00:12:47,934 --> 00:12:49,936
Don't put that in!

202
00:12:50,478 --> 00:12:52,021
We were just joking.

203
00:12:52,188 --> 00:12:54,482
If we put this in, the alcohol percentage would go down.

204
00:12:54,649 --> 00:12:55,483
ALCOHOL CONCENTRATION 60%

205
00:12:55,650 --> 00:12:58,361
It's stronger than disinfectant alcohol?

206
00:12:58,528 --> 00:13:00,697
That's not supposed to be drunk!

207
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:04,117
If we do a toast with that,
there's no guarantee we'll survive!

208
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:06,244
Now it's come down to this...

209
00:13:06,411 --> 00:13:08,997
Let's put some water in and act like nothing happened.

210
00:13:09,163 --> 00:13:11,749
Let's lower the alcohol percentage to a safe level.

211
00:13:11,916 --> 00:13:13,418
Hey, you guys go too.

212
00:13:13,584 --> 00:13:15,712
-Okay!
-Sure!

213
00:13:18,423 --> 00:13:20,717
My eyes!

214
00:13:21,718 --> 00:13:22,844
Are you okay?

215
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,513
I'm okay.

216
00:13:25,680 --> 00:13:28,307
Hey, hey! What are you doing?

217
00:13:28,474 --> 00:13:31,227
-Sorry.
-Don't worry about it.

218
00:13:31,394 --> 00:13:32,812
You’re not mad at me?

219
00:13:32,979 --> 00:13:36,274
No one in PaB would get mad
over something as trivial as that.

220
00:13:36,441 --> 00:13:37,567
Yokote...

221
00:13:37,734 --> 00:13:39,819
Then I'll put mine in too.

222
00:13:41,654 --> 00:13:45,366
-Hey, Iori!
-Knock it off!

223
00:13:45,533 --> 00:13:47,368
Elbowing you is okay, but not this?

224
00:13:47,535 --> 00:13:49,746
You're getting mad about the wrong thing!

225
00:13:50,413 --> 00:13:53,374
-Then at least...
-How about this?

226
00:13:53,541 --> 00:13:54,167
AWAMORI (60%)

227
00:13:54,375 --> 00:13:56,294
Well, I guess I can accept it.

228
00:13:56,461 --> 00:14:00,339
-Wait, you guys.
-You have to say a few words first.

229
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,008
Oh, you're right.

230
00:14:03,801 --> 00:14:05,011
What's wrong, Kohei?

231
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:07,221
I can't come up with anything.

232
00:14:07,388 --> 00:14:10,141
What? You're not good at things like this?

233
00:14:10,975 --> 00:14:12,935
What should I do?

234
00:14:13,936 --> 00:14:16,564
Why don't you introduce yourself?

235
00:14:16,731 --> 00:14:18,524
Okay. Then...

236
00:14:18,691 --> 00:14:21,944
I can say my name, my hobby, and my favorite quote.

237
00:14:22,111 --> 00:14:23,780
That's good enough.

238
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:25,782
All right, freshmen.

239
00:14:25,948 --> 00:14:27,575
Let's have a few words.

240
00:14:27,742 --> 00:14:29,952
-Okay.
-Name, hobby, favorite quote...

241
00:14:30,119 --> 00:14:32,538
Name, hobby, favorite quote...

242
00:14:34,916 --> 00:14:37,502
Thanks to this club, I realized how great--

243
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:40,755
-Kohei Imamura!
--is, even though I used to hate it.

244
00:14:40,922 --> 00:14:43,591
-Even though I got dragged into--
-Anime and games!

245
00:14:43,758 --> 00:14:46,344
--at first, I think it's really great now.

246
00:14:46,511 --> 00:14:48,971
I'll work hard so that someday,
I'll be able to say--

247
00:14:49,180 --> 00:14:53,476
-Kohei, marry me!
--I'm going to do my best!

248
00:14:53,643 --> 00:14:55,728
Knock it off!

249
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:59,398
-What are you doing?
-That's what I was about to say!

250
00:14:59,565 --> 00:15:01,484
That was a good speech.

251
00:15:01,651 --> 00:15:05,196
They talked about how they grew closer to each other.

252
00:15:08,324 --> 00:15:11,244
All right. Everyone has a drink, right?

253
00:15:11,410 --> 00:15:14,831
-They didn't have to fill it this full.
-Look, Kitahara.

254
00:15:14,997 --> 00:15:17,416
This explains how to do Otori right.

255
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,585
What? That means...

256
00:15:19,752 --> 00:15:21,295
If we show them this...

257
00:15:21,462 --> 00:15:23,965
We don't have to drink like this!

258
00:15:24,882 --> 00:15:26,759
Hey. Look at this.

259
00:15:28,010 --> 00:15:30,680
About Miyakojima Otori.

260
00:15:30,847 --> 00:15:33,558
The leader says a few words and takes a drink.

261
00:15:33,724 --> 00:15:36,060
After that, everyone drinks when it's their turn.

262
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:38,020
Finally, the leader drinks again,

263
00:15:38,187 --> 00:15:41,482
and says a few words again
before switching with the next leader.

264
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,776
This repeats for each person.

265
00:15:43,943 --> 00:15:46,529
-I see.
-That means...

266
00:15:46,696 --> 00:15:49,699
We have to do at least twelve toasts!

267
00:15:49,866 --> 00:15:51,826
We don't have enough alcohol for that.

268
00:15:51,993 --> 00:15:53,744
Let's put all of this in.

269
00:15:53,911 --> 00:15:56,539
I didn't expect that to happen!

270
00:15:56,706 --> 00:16:00,543
-We're used to strong drinks!
-You're right.

271
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:02,461
The important thing right now is...

272
00:16:02,628 --> 00:16:06,048
the strength of mind to avoid drowning in alcohol!

273
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:11,053
-Great, guys!
-That's it!

274
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,931
We've seen this many times already.

275
00:16:15,016 --> 00:16:18,019
-They look like they're having fun.
-This is so relaxing.

276
00:16:19,061 --> 00:16:20,062
What's wrong?

277
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:22,815
-We're out of booze.
-Already?

278
00:16:22,982 --> 00:16:26,027
No wonder. You drank so much.

279
00:16:27,236 --> 00:16:29,572
Thanks for going out to buy some.

280
00:16:29,739 --> 00:16:31,741
Sure.

281
00:16:31,908 --> 00:16:35,036
Sorry. Everyone else is drunk.

282
00:16:36,287 --> 00:16:38,915
It's too much to carry alone. Help me.

283
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:41,542
Oh, you're right.

284
00:16:43,211 --> 00:16:45,755
Hold on. What are you doing?

285
00:16:45,922 --> 00:16:48,799
Oh, sorry. I didn't notice.

286
00:16:52,261 --> 00:16:53,596
Aren't we going?

287
00:16:53,763 --> 00:16:56,307
I wasn't trying to tell you to put on your seatbelt!

288
00:17:02,021 --> 00:17:03,773
My first trip to a tropical island...

289
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,816
Night has arrived.

290
00:17:06,442 --> 00:17:09,820
The sky high above and the wide sea set me free...

291
00:17:10,613 --> 00:17:12,865
Maybe that's why...

292
00:17:13,032 --> 00:17:14,367
this idiot...

293
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,869
went outside naked.

294
00:17:20,539 --> 00:17:22,541
I can't believe this!

295
00:17:22,708 --> 00:17:25,836
I didn't notice. Don't be so mad.

296
00:17:26,128 --> 00:17:27,129
What's wrong?

297
00:17:27,296 --> 00:17:30,258
He got out of the car dressed like that!

298
00:17:30,424 --> 00:17:32,593
It was really warm.

299
00:17:33,552 --> 00:17:34,887
No wonder.

300
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:37,723
Resorts feel so liberating.

301
00:17:37,890 --> 00:17:39,225
It happens a lot.

302
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:42,103
Why are you all agreeing with Iori?

303
00:17:42,436 --> 00:17:45,982
-But, Cakey, think about it.
-What?

304
00:17:46,357 --> 00:17:50,486
A tropical island, a starry sky,
going for a drive with a guy...

305
00:17:50,653 --> 00:17:53,197
These are the memories of youth you wanted, right?

306
00:17:53,364 --> 00:17:56,033
Maybe if the guy wasn't a half-naked pervert.

307
00:17:56,617 --> 00:17:58,286
I see. Sorry.

308
00:17:58,452 --> 00:18:01,539
-Do you understand now?
-But even for me...

309
00:18:01,706 --> 00:18:05,418
-Going fully naked is hard.
-I wasn't trying to say you didn't strip enough!

310
00:18:05,584 --> 00:18:08,713
You don't have to take your clothes off
when you drink, do you?

311
00:18:08,879 --> 00:18:11,757
Stop looking at me like you don't know
what I'm talking about!

312
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:15,303
Hey, hey. Have a drink and relax.

313
00:18:15,469 --> 00:18:17,305
Come on.

314
00:18:17,471 --> 00:18:19,348
That's my...

315
00:18:25,980 --> 00:18:27,773
What was in that?

316
00:18:27,940 --> 00:18:30,026
The leftovers from Otori.

317
00:18:30,192 --> 00:18:32,987
I diluted it though.

318
00:18:33,154 --> 00:18:36,282
But it's still over 30 percent.

319
00:18:36,616 --> 00:18:38,242
But this isn't bad either.

320
00:18:38,409 --> 00:18:40,453
It's quiet now.

321
00:18:40,995 --> 00:18:42,913
-What?
-You woke up?

322
00:18:45,625 --> 00:18:47,168
Hey, Iori.

323
00:18:47,710 --> 00:18:50,212
-What's wrong?
-Iori, you're...

324
00:18:50,379 --> 00:18:52,715
-really dull, aren't you?
-What do you mean?

325
00:18:52,882 --> 00:18:54,508
What's dull about me?

326
00:18:54,675 --> 00:18:56,218
You are dull!

327
00:18:56,385 --> 00:18:59,930
You didn't notice
what I was trying to tell you.

328
00:19:00,973 --> 00:19:02,892
What are you talking about?

329
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:04,727
I thought about it.

330
00:19:04,894 --> 00:19:08,189
You're dull, so you wouldn't get it even if I told you.

331
00:19:08,481 --> 00:19:10,775
I have to show you through my actions.

332
00:19:11,817 --> 00:19:15,237
Cakey, are we about to get to the true end?

333
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:19,241
I can't take it anymore!
If you don't get it no matter what I say,

334
00:19:19,408 --> 00:19:21,077
then I'll just--

335
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:24,372
I'll watch. Take it off.

336
00:19:24,580 --> 00:19:26,582
Oh, so that's what you meant.

337
00:19:27,249 --> 00:19:31,253
-Now that you say that--
-Oh, I see. I see.

338
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:33,047
Or else...

339
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:35,633
I'll take it off for you!

340
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:38,135
Wait! Calm down!

341
00:19:38,302 --> 00:19:40,179
You're next, Kohei!

342
00:19:40,346 --> 00:19:41,138
What?

343
00:19:45,559 --> 00:19:46,644
That was bad.

344
00:19:46,811 --> 00:19:49,980
It was just one drink. She totally changed.

345
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:53,109
If you hadn't gotten out of the car naked--

346
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:55,861
Then you should have gone shopping!

347
00:19:57,655 --> 00:19:59,156
There you are!

348
00:19:59,323 --> 00:20:00,616
Oh, no!

349
00:20:04,662 --> 00:20:06,455
Oh, dear...

350
00:20:06,622 --> 00:20:09,500
I can't get TV reception.

351
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:12,712
-You're recording it anyway, right?
-You bastard.

352
00:20:12,878 --> 00:20:15,673
Don't you know it's important to see it live?

353
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:18,134
-No.
-But...

354
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,386
Now that I think about it...

355
00:20:22,430 --> 00:20:26,183
I never imagined I'd join a club like this.

356
00:20:26,350 --> 00:20:28,727
I think it suits you well.

357
00:20:28,894 --> 00:20:30,938
Are you trying to start a fight?

358
00:20:31,105 --> 00:20:34,442
I joined because you tricked me!

359
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:36,944
I tricked you? Don't say that.

360
00:20:37,111 --> 00:20:39,405
Are you trying to say it's not true?

361
00:20:39,572 --> 00:20:42,199
-No.
-Hurry up and go.

362
00:20:42,366 --> 00:20:45,119
Your wish came true, right?

363
00:20:45,286 --> 00:20:47,455
-What do you mean?
-You said it, right?

364
00:20:47,621 --> 00:20:52,418
You said you thought the life of your dreams
was waiting for you at college.

365
00:20:54,170 --> 00:20:57,923
This is like a dream, right?

366
00:21:02,219 --> 00:21:04,180
Yeah. You're right.

367
00:21:04,889 --> 00:21:08,100
-More like a nightmare than a dream.
-That's right.

368
00:21:08,267 --> 00:21:11,854
What? You don't know when to give up!

369
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,494
Chii-chan, where did you get those?

370
00:21:26,660 --> 00:21:28,454
At the convenience store.

371
00:21:28,621 --> 00:21:31,040
Wow, nice shot.

372
00:21:31,207 --> 00:21:33,209
The image quality is good, but...

373
00:21:40,007 --> 00:21:41,467
What a huge gap.

374
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:44,094
I like both of them.

375
00:21:44,261 --> 00:21:47,097
That's exactly how we are.

376
00:23:55,893 --> 00:23:57,686
What are they doing?
